com.sun.xml.ws.commons.virtualbox
Class IProgress

java.lang.Object
  com.sun.xml.ws.commons.virtualbox.IProgress

public class IProgress
extends Object

The IProgress interface represents a task progress object that allows to wait for the completion of some asynchronous task. The task consists of one or more operations that run sequentially, one after one. There is an individual percent of completion of the current operation and the percent of completion of the task as a whole. Similarly, you can wait for the completion of a particular operation or for the completion of the whole task. Every operation is identified by a number (starting from 0) and has a separate description.
